Function Reference/sanitize title for query « WordPress Codex
-----------

Sanitizes a title with the 'query' context. Used for querying the
database for a value from URL. Shorthand for
`sanitize_title($title, "", "query")` (See
[sanitize\_title()](/Function_Reference/sanitize_title "Function Reference/sanitize title")).

Usage
-----

    <?php sanitize_title_for_query( $title ); ?>

Parameters
----------

 `$title` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The string to be sanitized
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   Sanitized string.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

Since `sanitize_title_for_query()` calls `sanitize_title()`, the
[sanitize\_title](/Plugin_API/Filter_Reference/sanitize_title "Plugin API/Filter Reference/sanitize title")
filter is applied with a context of 'query'.

Change Log
----------

Since: [1.0.0](/Version_1.0 "Version 1.0")

Source File
-----------

`sanitize_title_for_query()` is located in
`/wp-includes/formatting.php`.

